#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_packetpeerudp.rst:127
msgid ""
"Makes this ``PacketPeerUDP`` listen on the ``port`` binding to "
"``bind_address`` with a buffer size ``recv_buf_size``."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_packetpeerudp.rst:129
msgid ""
"If ``bind_address`` is set to ``\"*\"`` (default), the peer will listen "
"on all available addresses (both IPv4 and IPv6)."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_packetpeerudp.rst:131
msgid ""
"If ``bind_address`` is set to ``\"0.0.0.0\"`` (for IPv4) or ``\"::\"`` "
"(for IPv6), the peer will listen on all available addresses matching that"
" IP type."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_packetpeerudp.rst:133
msgid ""
"If ``bind_address`` is set to any valid address (e.g. "
"``\"192.168.1.101\"``, ``\"::1\"``, etc), the peer will only listen on "
"the interface with that addresses (or fail if no interface with the given"
" address exists)."
msgstr ""

